Package: move2UD
Title: Dynamic Brownian Bridge Movement Models for move2 Objects
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bart", "Kranstauber", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "b.kranstauber@uva.nl"),
    person("Kamran", "Safi", role = "aut"),
    person("Anne K.", "Scharf", role = "aut"),
    person("Marco", "Smolla", role = "ctb"))
Description: Dynamic Brownian Bridge Movement Models (dBBMM) and dynamic
    Bivariate Gaussian Bridge (dBGB) models for estimating utilisation
    distributions and movement variance from animal tracking data. This
    package provides the dBBMM/dBGB functionality previously available in
    the 'move' package, migrated to work with 'move2', 'sf', and 'terra'
    objects. The C computational kernels are preserved from the original
    implementation; the R interface layer has been rewritten for the
    modern spatial stack.
